FBIS4-57019 "drlat092_c_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 MEXICO Drug Trafficker Receives 40-Year Sentence Drug Trafficker Receives 40-Year Sentence PA1105163894 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0430 GMT 11 May 94 PA1105163894 Mexico City XEW Television Network Spanish BFN [Report by Salvador Chavez from the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] Drug trafficker Miguel Angel Felix Gallardo, imprisoned in the Almoloya de Juarez Prison, will remain in jail at least until the year 2,034. Here is Salvador Chavez with a report: [Begin recording] [Chavez] Raul Felipe Garza, from the Attorney General's Office in Jalisco, has revealed that Miguel Angel Felix Gallardo, considered one of the most notorious drug trafficking capos in Mexico and the Medellin Cartel's contact in Mexico, was sentenced to 40 years in prison by the fourth district court judge. Garza explained that Felix Gallardo was tried for the murders of U.S. DEA agent Enrique Camarena Salazar and Mexican pilot Alfredo Savala Avelar. [Garza] Felix Gallardo received a 40-year sentence, and the Special Prosecutor's Office has agreed with this decision. [Chavez] Was any appeal filed regarding compensation for damages or the fine? [Garza] He was sentenced to 40 years in prison, fined 1,485 new pesos, and asked to pay some 1,550 new pesos in compensation for damages. [Chavez] Felix Gallardo was accused of planning the kidnapping and murder of U.S. DEA agent Camarena and Mexican pilot Savala Avelar on 8 February 1985. He was accused of crimes of homicide, kidnapping, and torture. [end recording]
